# Vendored: @imgly/background-removal (1.7.0) + data assets

## License

This directory contains source code and data from `@imgly/background-removal`,
licensed under the **GNU Affero General Public License v3.0** (AGPL-3.0). See
`LICENSE.md` in this directory for the full license text.

Vendoring this library is the reason the entire NoAdsPhotos project is
AGPL-3.0 (the license cascades — see the project root `LICENSE`).

Per AGPL §13, users interacting with the deployed site must be offered the
corresponding source code. This is provided via:
- The "Source" link in the site footer (links to the project repo).
- The privacy page (`/privacy.html`) which links to the source repo.
- A direct attribution in `/THIRD-PARTY.md`.

## What's vendored here

Everything required for the bg-remove feature to work after a clean
`git clone && npm install && npm run serve` is committed to this directory.
No deploy-time install step is required.

| File pattern                              | Source                                                              | Purpose |
| ----------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------- | --- |
| `index.mjs` (~170 KB)                     | `@imgly/background-removal@1.7.0` npm tarball, `dist/index.mjs`     | Main ESM bundle (lazy-imported by `js/ops/bgremove.js`). |
| `LICENSE.md` (~34 KB)                     | `@imgly/background-removal@1.7.0` npm tarball, `LICENSE.md`         | Full AGPL-3.0 license text. |
| `resources.json` (~9 KB)                  | `staticimgly.com/@imgly/background-removal-data/1.7.0/dist/resources.json`, **trimmed** to the keys we serve | Manifest mapping logical keys to a list of content-addressable chunks. The trimmed copy lists ONLY the five keys we ship (see below). |
| 33 SHA-256-named binary files (~117 MB)   | `staticimgly.com/@imgly/background-removal-data/1.7.0/dist/{hash}`   | The chunked binary data for each key in `resources.json`. The bundle fetches these by hash, concatenates them in memory, and feeds the result to ONNX Runtime Web. |

### Why the chunks are named by hash

`@imgly` ships its data CDN as a content-addressable store: each chunk's file
name is the SHA-256 of its bytes. The bundle fetches `resources.json`,
joins each chunk's name with `publicPath`, and verifies sizes against the
manifest. We preserve this layout exactly so the unmodified upstream
`index.mjs` works without patching. Filenames are deterministic across
versions (same bytes → same name) — re-running
`scripts/install-bgremove.mjs` is idempotent.

### Keys we vendor (CPU + WebGPU)

The upstream `resources.json` references seven keys totalling ~344 MB.
We ship five — the ones any modern browser path can need at runtime:

| Key                                                       | Size      | Chunks | Purpose |
| --------------------------------------------------------- | --------- | ------ | --- |
| `/models/isnet_fp16`                                      | 84.07 MB  | 22     | The fp16-quantized ISNET segmentation model — the variant `js/ops/bgremove.js` requests via `config.model`. Shared by both execution providers. |
| `/onnxruntime-web/ort-wasm-simd-threaded.wasm`            | 11.27 MB  | 3      | ONNX Runtime Web's compiled WASM kernel for the CPU SIMD execution provider (threaded). |
| `/onnxruntime-web/ort-wasm-simd-threaded.mjs`             | 0.02 MB   | 1      | ONNX Runtime Web's JavaScript glue for the CPU kernel above. |
| `/onnxruntime-web/ort-wasm-simd-threaded.jsep.wasm`       | 21.95 MB  | 6      | ONNX Runtime Web's compiled WASM kernel for the WebGPU/JSEP execution provider. |
| `/onnxruntime-web/ort-wasm-simd-threaded.jsep.mjs`        | 0.05 MB   | 1      | ONNX Runtime Web's JavaScript glue for the WebGPU/JSEP kernel above. |

Browsers fetch only the variant they actually need:
- **CPU-only browsers** (no `navigator.gpu`) pull the non-jsep wasm+mjs.
- **WebGPU-capable browsers** pull the jsep wasm+mjs.

Both paths share the same model file. So real-world first-use bandwidth is
either ~95 MB (CPU) or ~106 MB (WebGPU), not the full ~118 MB.

The other two upstream keys are intentionally **not** vendored:
- `/models/isnet` (full precision, 176 MB) — too large; fp16 is visually identical for our use case.
- `/models/isnet_quint8` (44 MB) — saves ~44 MB but degrades edge quality; we picked fp16 as a quality/size sweet spot.

If you want any of these, run `node scripts/install-bgremove.mjs` after
adding the corresponding key to `KEEP_KEYS` in that script, and update this
notice + `THIRD-PARTY.md` accordingly.

